Consider the following two undirected graphs:

Graph G1: 

Vertices = {a, b, c, d}

Edges = {(a,b), (b,c), (c,d), (d,a), (a,c)}

Graph G2:

Vertices = {1, 2, 3, 4}

Edges = {(1,2), (2,3), (3,4), (4,1), (1,3)}

Determine whether G1 and G2 are isomorphic or not. If they are isomorphic, provide an isomorphism between them.
